external_knowledge:
- 'high-performing' refers to students with a GPA greater than 3.0;
- 'recently' refers to students admitted after January 1, 2019;
- 'academic streams' and 'branches' refer to the program and specialization areas, respectively.

sql:
SELECT stream_name 
FROM streams 
WHERE minimum_credits_required > 120;

external_knowledge:
- Guiding lights refer to faculty members; 
- Budding engineers refer to students in the Mechanical Engineering branch; 
- First beacon of knowledge refers to the first faculty member listed alphabetically for each student based on their course enrollments.

sql:
SELECT AVG(CAST(s.gpa AS REAL)) AS Average_GPA
FROM students s
WHERE s.student_id IN (SELECT f.faculty_id FROM faculties f);

